==English==

===Etymology===
From New Latin ''ad hoc'' "for this".

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]:
**UK: /ˈæd ˈhɒk/ 
**US: /ˈæd ˈhɑk/, /ˈæd ˈhɔk/, /ˈɑd ˈhɑk/
*{{audio|en-us-ad hoc.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''[[ad]] [[hoc]]'''
# for this particular purpose
# special
# created on the spur of the moment, impromptu

